title: As a TRICARE beneficiary, have you ever thought about how your experiences at ... - Instagram
description:
0 likes, 0 comments - wbamcpao on May 13, 2025: "As a TRICARE beneficiary, have you ever thought about how your experiences at William Beaumont Army Medical Center (WBAMC) could help improve care for others? Now's your chance to make a difference.

TRICARE beneficiaries can volunteer to join the PFPC and partner directly with WBAMC staff to co-create solutions that truly matter.

Join us for our next Patient and Family Partnership Council (PFPC) meeting:
Date: Wednesday, May 21, 2025
Time: 10 a.m.
Where: Clinical Assembly Room, 1st Floor, Administration Building (Main Campus)
Or Watch Live on Facebook!

The PFPC is where patients, family members, and staff come together to listen, learn, and lead. By sharing stories, ideas, and feedback, YOU help shape a better care experience not only for yourselfbut for every TRICARE beneficiary who walks through our doors.

Because your experience matters. Your ideas matter. Your voice matters.

#WBAMC #PFPC #MilitaryMedicine #PatientExperience #TRICARE #ElPaso #MHS #ArmyMedicine #YourVoiceMatters".

title: Thousands in West Region being booted out of military's Tricare | Veterans of Foreign Wars (VFW)
description:

title: Half my claims this year denied- Tricare states I am not insured by them - Reddit
description:
We added one of the providers onto the call, and discovered that Tricare has switched their claims center from Wisconsin to South Carolina.
I've been having an absolutey awful time with Humana military/Tricare east this year, after 3 previous years with no trouble.
They resubmit the claims, and Tricare comes back and says something to the effect of "patient could not be identified as ours".
I got claim numbers from the providers and asked Tricare about them and they said they had no record of them.
When I told the Tricare rep I wanted to do that she said that wasn't allowed and they could only talk to provider claims.
text:
Update: I spoke to Tricare again and was able to get somewhere. We added one of the providers onto the call, and discovered that Tricare has switched their claims center from Wisconsin to South Carolina. My provider was unaware and had mailed my claim to Wisconsin. If anyone else in the east region is having a similar issue, I can provide the new address, fax number, and payer ID that your provider will need to submit a claim to the right location.

Thank you to whoever takes the time to read this. I've been having an absolutey awful time with Humana military/Tricare east this year, after 3 previous years with no trouble.

I have 3 providers after me for a combined total of 30,000 in medical bills that should be Tricare's responsibility. Two of these are providers I have been seeing for years with no issues.

I talk to their billing departments and go over how the claim was submitted, making sure they use my correct benefits number and other personal info. They resubmit the claims, and Tricare comes back and says something to the effect of "patient could not be identified as ours".

So I call Tricare. They are adamant that I am insured, evidenced by the claims that have been approved this year, some from the same providers on the same day as the one that are getting denied. They saiy it is an issue with how the providers are submitting the claim.

I can see the approved claims in my EOB, but the denied claims don't show up at all. I got claim numbers from the providers and asked Tricare about them and they said they had no record of them.

The providers are adamant that the claims are submitted correctly. One even offered to go on a 3 way call with me to try to get it straightened out. When I told the Tricare rep I wanted to do that she said that wasn't allowed and they could only talk to provider claims.

Now I feel backed into a corner with no idea what to do next and terrified these bills will fall on me. What can I do next at this point in the process?

I haven't been sent to collections yet but one of the providers is starting to get a little more aggressive.

title: TRICARE mental health provider. No payments since January - Reddit
description:
File one through your Senator's office, Rick Scott or Ashley Moody, and file one through the House.
If you notified your Tricare Liaison through the portal and haven't gotten not gotten a response.
Ask them to verify you sent a secure message to your Tricare Liaison in the portal and haven't gotten a response in 15 days.
Availity shows Paid claims and check numbers but zero payments have come to me.
 Cherry Nelson | Claims Reviewer|TriWest Healthcare Alliance Claims Administration O: (623) 473-8071 Fax: (866) 437-1216 E: cnelson4@triwest.com www.triwest.com
text:
File a congressional through both chambers of Congress. File one through your Senator's office, Rick Scott or Ashley Moody, and file one through the House. Don't just go after Tricare itself but go after Humana as well as Defense Health Agency. Not sure who your representative is in Florida but getting other chambers involved will definitely get a response from DHA and Humana Tricare.

I'm currently working one through Tennessee via Senator Blackburn's office and Congressman Burchett's office.

If you notified your Tricare Liaison through the portal and haven't gotten not gotten a response.

Call the Provider Portal Helpdesk in the East Region 800-444-5445. Ask them to verify you sent a secure message to your Tricare Liaison in the portal and haven't gotten a response in 15 days.

Verify you have the correct Payor ID for Tricare (it changed on Jan 1st)

If you are an LCSW the new claims processor may have incorrectly denied claims for you not filing out the CMS 1500 block 17 with a supervising MD/DO.

I haven't gotten paid either; LPC in TX. I haven't made phone calls to my republican reps office or called triwest. Yesterday there were a flurry of emails until I got an email from someone helpful! She said she's checking with PGBA to see where my payments are going. Availity shows Paid claims and check numbers but zero payments have come to me. I get paid just fine thru triwest for CCN VA clients. Here's their info; hope it helps. 

Cherry Nelson | Claims Reviewer|TriWest Healthcare Alliance Claims Administration O: (623) 473-8071 Fax: (866) 437-1216 E: cnelson4@triwest.com www.triwest.com
